		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">OODA Loop</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>OODA Loop</b> (for <b>Observe</b>, <b>Orient</b>, <b>Decide</b> and <b>Act</b>) is a concept applied to the <a href="/wiki/Combat_operations_process" title="Combat operations process">combat operations process</a>, often at <a href="/wiki/Strategic" title="Strategic" class="mw-redirect">strategic</a> level in both the military and commercial operations. It was created by <a href="/wiki/Military_strategy" title="Military strategy">military strategist</a> and <a href="/wiki/United_States_Air_Force" title="United States Air Force">USAF</a> Colonel <a href="/wiki/John_Boyd_(military_strategist)" title="John Boyd (military strategist)">John Boyd</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
